TEDx charts: code

library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
events <- read_csv("ted.csv")
themes <- readxl::read_excel("type2.xlsx")
ted_aa_type <- readxl::read_excel("type_of_event_per city asia_americas.xlsx")

Bar: themes

ted_aa_type %>%
  mutate(city = str_to_title(city)) %>%
  mutate(continent = str_to_title(continent)) %>%
  mutate(type = str_to_title(type)) %>%
  group_by(continent, city, type) %>%
  mutate(total = sum(type_num)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(-year, -type_num) %>%
  unique() %>%
  mutate(city = str_replace(city, "Washington Dc", "Washington, DC")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(city, total, group = type, fill=type)) +
    geom_col(position = "dodge", width = 0.7, alpha = 0.9) +
    theme_light() +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) +
    paletteer::scale_fill_paletteer_d("yarrr::appletv") +
    theme(
      panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
      panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "#606060"),
      panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
      panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
      panel.border = element_blank(),
      panel.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
      plot.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
      legend.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
      legend.key = element_rect(colour = "black"),
      text = element_text(family="Avenir", color = "white"),
      axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = -0.5, size = rel(1.25), color = "white"),
      axis.text.y = element_text(size = rel(1.5), color = "white"),
      axis.title = element_text(size = rel(1.25), color="white"),
      axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
      legend.title = element_text(size = rel(1.25)),
      legend.text = element_text(size = rel(1)),
      legend.position = "bottom",
      axis.line = element_line(color = "#606060"),
      axis.line.x = element_line(color = "white", size = 0.35),
      plot.title.position = "plot",
      plot.title = element_text(size = rel(2.25), face="bold"),
      plot.subtitle = element_text(size = rel(1.75))
      ) +
    labs(
      x = "", 
      y = "Number of TEDx Talks\n",
      fill = NULL,
      title = "Figure 3.3: Type of TEDx Talks by Top American and Asian Cities",
      subtitle = "Talks from 2009-2018\n")

Line: 2 continents

events %>%
  filter(macro_region %in% c("Americas", "Asia")) %>%
  select(country, city, macro_region, year) %>%
  group_by(macro_region, year) %>%
  mutate(yearly_count = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(year, yearly_count, group=macro_region)) +

Bar: month frequency

events %>%
  select(date, city, country, lat, lon, macro_region, meso_region, development_level, gdp_per_capita, hdi, ECI, population, year) %>%
  mutate(city = str_to_title(city)) %>%
  mutate(country = str_to_title(country)) %>%
  mutate(date = as.POSIXct(date, format="%m/%d/%Y")) %>%
  group_by(country, city) %>%
  mutate(ted_per_city = n()) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(year != "2019") %>%
  filter(!is.na(macro_region)) %>%
  mutate(month = months(date, abbr=T)) %>%
  mutate(month = factor(month, levels = month.abb)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(month, fill=macro_region)) +
  geom_histogram(stat = "count", alpha = 0.9) +
  paletteer::scale_fill_paletteer_d("yarrr::appletv") +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) +
  facet_wrap(~year) +
  theme_minimal() +
    theme(
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "#606060"),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
        legend.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
        legend.key = element_rect(colour = "black"),
        text = element_text(family="Avenir", color = "white"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 8.5, color = "white"),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 10, color="white"),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        legend.title = element_text(size = rel(1.15)),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 10),
        legend.position = "bottom",
        strip.text = element_text(size = rel(1.25), color = "white"),
        panel.spacing = unit(3, "lines"),
        axis.line = element_line(color = "#606060"),
        plot.title = element_text(size = rel(2.25), face="bold"),
        plot.title.position = "plot") +
  labs(
    fill = NULL,
    x = NULL, 
    y = "Number of TEDx Talks\n",
    title = "Figure 4.2: Which Months Have the Most TEDx Talks?\n")

Line: top 10 American and Asian countries

events %>% 
  mutate(city = str_to_title(city)) %>%
  mutate(city = str_replace(city, "Washington, Dc", "Washington, DC")) %>%
  filter(city %in% c("Los Angeles", "New York", "Toronto", "Sao Paolo", "Washington, DC", "Beijing", "Bengal", "Mumbai", "Seoul", "Singapore")) %>%
  group_by(year, city) %>% 
  summarise(ted_per_city = sum(ted_per_city)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = ted_per_city)) +
  geom_line(size=1, color = "#E62B1E") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(2009, 2018)) +
  facet_wrap(~city, scales = "free") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = "#606060", size = 1),
    plot.title = element_text(size = rel(2.25), face="bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = rel(1.75)),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "black"),
    panel.spacing = unit(3, "lines"),
    text=element_text(family="Avenir", color = "white"),
    strip.text = element_text(size = rel(1.25), color = "white")) +
  labs(title = "Figure 3.4: TEDx Talks in Top American and Asian Cities",
       subtitle = "Talks from 2009-2018\n",
       x = NULL,
       y = NULL)

Calendar heatmap: 2009-2018

source("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/iascchen/VisHealth/master/R/calendarHeat.R")

ted_heat <- events %>%
  mutate(date = as.POSIXct(date, format="%m/%d/%Y")) %>%
  dplyr::count(year, date, sort=T)

reds <- rev(c("#a50f15", "#E62B1E", "#fb6a4a", "#fc9272", "#fcbba1", "#fee5d9"))

ted_heat13 <- ted_heat %>% filter(year %in% c("2009", "2010", "2011", "2012", "2013"))
calendarHeat(ted_heat13$date, ted_heat13$n, ncolors = 99, color = "reds", varname="Figure 4.1: TEDx Talks")

ted_heat18 <- ted_heat %>% filter(year %in% c("2014", "2015", "2016", "2017", "2018"))
calendarHeat(ted_heat18$date, ted_heat18$n, ncolors = 99, color = "reds", varname="TEDx Talks")
